  "title": "Limit category list to 3 specific items",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js, I could not find what I was looking for which is: \r\nI have 10 categories onn the left side and i would like to show 3 specific categories on the left side category section. Anyidea how i can pass the list to display on the left side?\r\nI would like to display \"Beers\", \"cider\", and \"howlers\" on this list only and not every category that  i have.\r\n\t/* Categories refinement widget */\r\n\t\t\tsearch.addWidget(\r\n\t\t\t\tinstantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n\t\t\t\t\tcontainer: '#facet-categories',\r\n\t\t\t\t\tattributeName: 'taxonomies_hierarchical.product_cat.lvl0',\r\n\t\t\t\t\tseparator: ' > ',\r\n\t\t\t\t\tsortBy: ['count:desc', 'name:asc'],\r\n'taxonomies_hierarchical.product_cat.lvl1', 'taxonomies_hierarchical.product_cat.lvl2'],\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\ttemplates: {\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\theader: '<h4>' + algolia.woocommerce.i18n.product_categories + '</h4>'\r\n\t\t\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t\t\t})\r\n\t\t\t);",
